<p>
<center>
<img style="float:right;margin-left:20px;margin-bottom:20px" src="https://storage.googleapis.com/ff-storage-p01/press_kits/posters/001/135/161/original/bc68d63648-poster.jpg?1530943487" width="200" height="300" />
</center>
</p>

<p>This long-form research documentary focuses on the controversy surrounding a commemorative statue of Edward Cornwallis, the man credited with founding the city of Halifax, Nova Scotia.   His mistreatment of the Miâ€™kmaq indigenous population has been classified as genocide. The film was screened to a crowded house at Victoria College in the University of Toronto.  It features interviews with historians, city councillors, and journalists.</p>



